						<div class="postbody">I've tended to refer to one sample per pitch as the &quot;Mellotron&quot; pattern. There are valid reasons to use it even without hardware limits like that of the NES or Neo Geo sample unit. One is that an instrument may have greatly differing tonalities in the high or low pitches.</div>

